.Dd September 7, 2018
.Dt DTCH 1
.Os "Causal Agency"
.
.Sh NAME
.Nm dtch ,
.Nm atch
.Nd detached sessions
.
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar name Op Ar command ...
.Nm atch
.Op Ar name
.
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
spawns the
.Ar command
(by default, the user's shell)
inside a new PTY.
It then lends control of the detached PTY to
.Nm atch
over a UNIX-domain socket.
.Nm
should be run as a background job or with
.Xr nohup 1 .
.
.Pp
.Nm atch
attaches to the
.Nm
session with the corresponding
.Ar name .
To detach from a session, type
.Ic ^Q .
.
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag
.It Pa ~/.dtch/ Ns Ar name
UNIX-domain socket for the session
.Ar name .
.El
.
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal -offset indent
dtch foo vim &
atch foo
.Ed
.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr nohup 1 ,
.Xr screen 1 ,
.Xr forkpty 3
